CHAT.comment: MOT wants to read the book again to refresh her memory. Chi remembers many details about the story and relays them to her. Mot bends over backwards to give Chi ideas for his letter. They discuss Eric Carle's illustrations , what he might have been like as a child , where he got the idea for his book , etc. Mot keeps suggesting that Chi put some of these ideas down on paper , but Chi seems to have trouble doing that. When he does write sentences down Mot helps him with spelling and punctuation , although sometimes her punctuation is incorrect. Mot is very patient and very involved in the task. She is also very caught up in small details. She reads some of the sentences in Chi's letter out loud so he can see if they sound right. There is often much discussion over a single phrase. That is probably why the task took 45 minutes to complete.
